FAQs
What are the basic requirements to study medicine in Italy?
The basic requirements include a high school diploma with strong grades in science subjects, language proficiency (usually in English), and passing the IMAT exam specific to the university.

Is studying medicine in Italy expensive?
Tuition fees and living expenses in Italy are generally lower compared to Western countries. Scholarships and financial aid can also help reduce costs.

How can I apply for scholarships to study in Italy?
You can apply for scholarships through the universities, as well as through Italian government programs and private organizations. Qadri-International can assist you in finding and applying for suitable scholarships.

Are degrees from Italian medical universities recognized worldwide?
Yes, degrees from Italian medical universities are widely recognized and respected globally. Graduates often have the qualifications needed to practice medicine in various countries around the world.

What support can Qadri-International provide for prospective medical students?
Qadri-International offers comprehensive support, including university selection, application assistance, visa processing, and pre-departure guidance, ensuring a smooth and successful journey to studying medicine abroad.
